The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 July is 45,671 (5,263.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 June, there were 1,173 new confirmed cases (135.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 June, there were 670 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 75% (503 extra cases).
